You Can Install A Graphical Desktop Environment For Example GNOME KDE Plasma Cinnamon XFCE Mate LXQT LXDE And More Using sudo apt install
You Can Also Install A Window Manager That Is Customizable Like i3wm swaywm icewm bspwm dwm etc using sudo apt install

For Hyprland You can Use Kool Hyprland
1. Prepare Your System
   Update packages:
   sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
   Enable universe repository (needed for Wayland packages):
   sudo add-apt-repository universe
   sudo apt update
2. Install Dependencies
   Hyprland requires Wayland libraries, wlroots, and build tools:
   sudo apt install -y build-essential cmake meson ninja-build \
   pkg-config libwayland-dev libx11-dev libx11-xcb-dev \
   libxcb1-dev libxcb-composite0-dev libxcb-xfixes0-dev \
   libxcb-render0-dev libxcb-shape0-dev libxcb-xkb-dev \
   libxkbcommon-dev libxkbcommon-x11-dev libpixman-1-dev \
   libegl-dev libgles2-mesa-dev libdrm-dev libgbm-dev \
   libinput-dev libudev-dev libseat-dev libpam0g-dev \
   libpipewire-0.3-dev libavutil-dev libavcodec-dev \
   libavformat-dev libavfilter-dev libswscale-dev \
   libgtk-3-dev libgtk-4-dev

3. Install Hyprland (KooL Script)
JaKooLit maintains an Ubuntu‑Hyprland installer that automates setup
git clone https://github.com/JaKooLit/Ubuntu-Hyprland.git
cd Ubuntu-Hyprland
./install.sh

4. Configure Hyprland

    Default config is placed in ~/.config/hypr/.

    You can edit hyprland.conf to adjust:

        Keybindings

        Window gaps and animations

        Monitor layout

    Waybar config is in ~/.config/waybar/.

5. Launch Hyprland

    Log out of your current session.

    At the login manager (GDM, LightDM, etc.), select Hyprland (Wayland).

    If you’re using startx, you can create a .xinitrc with:
    exec Hyprland

If you want to install unity you can install using sudo apt install ubuntu-unity-desktop

If LightDM Cant Detect Your Desktop Environment I Would Recommend Lightdm gtk greeter this can be confirmed by running sudo apt install lightdm-gtk-greeter

Then Have Fun And Start Using A Graphical Desktop Environment
